\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}_{i}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $1\leq i\leq d+2$
\end_inset

, hence we have
\begin_inset Formula $+1$
\end_inset

vector than total number of dimensions (our space is 
\begin_inset Formula $d+1$
\end_inset

-dimensional).
 Accori to the theory of vector spaces when we have more vectors than dimensions
 of the space then they are linearly dependent (one of the vectors is a
 linear combination of the others).
 Which means that for instance our extra point 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}_{d+2}$
\end_inset

, can be compute by the equation (in 
\begin_inset Formula $d+1$
\end_inset

-dimensional space): 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{x}_{d+2}=\sum_{i=1}^{d+1}a_{i}\mathbf{x}_{i}
\]

\end_inset

We need to get 
